 tips for making your move to the cloud lets get started resume transcript autoscroll related courses preview course learning sharepoint 00 with simon allardice h m beginner contents notebook search this course clear search search introduction welcome s  cloud computing basics what is cloud computing m s exploring the components of the cloud m s understanding the infrastructure of the cloud m s cloud services overview m s using storage and database services m s  evaluate whether cloud computing is right for your business the three main cloud computing scenarios m s the operational benefits of the cloud m s the economic benefits of the cloud m s the staffing benefits of the cloud m s understanding the security risks of cloud computing m s  explore cloud storage overview of storage as a service m s about storage providers m s understanding cloud storage security m s cloud storage considerations m s  explore cloud tools exploring google apps m s taking a look at microsoft windows live m s working with skydrive m s syncing with icloud m 0s using dropbox m s working with evernote m s exploring asana m s staying organized with highrise m s using prezi m s working with yammer m s  migrate to the cloud making a cloud migration plan m s analyzing service and service providers m s releasing data using the wave approach m s securing data m s establishing a training plan for staff and other stakeholders m s predicting and responding to change m s  evaluate cloud performance in your business monitoring performance after transitioning to the cloud m s finetuning cloud use m s additional resources m s conclusion where to go from here s show moreshow less mark as unwatched mark all as unwatched are you sure you want to mark all the videos in this course as unwatched this will not affect your course history your reports or your certificates of completion for this course mark all as unwatched cancel take notes with your new membership type in the entry box then click enter to save yo